# 詞: 銀包

1. 我個銀包遺失喺巴士上，而家好驚。 (I lost my wallet on the bus, and I'm very worried now.)
2. 佢個銀包好舊，但係佢好鍾意用。 (His wallet is very old, but he likes using it.)
3. 你個銀包入面有幾多錢？ (How much money is in your wallet?)
4. 我剛剛買咗一個新銀包，係真皮㗎。 (I just bought a new wallet; it's made of genuine leather.)
5. 唔好將銀包放喺後袋，容易被人偷。 (Don't put your wallet in your back pocket; it's easy to get stolen.)
6. 佢個銀包好薄，因為佢只係帶咗幾張紙幣。 (His wallet is very thin because he only brought a few banknotes.)
7. 我個銀包被扒手偷咗，連身份證都冇咗。 (My wallet was stolen by a pickpocket, and even my ID card is gone.)
8. 呢個銀包好靚，係我生日禮物。 (This wallet is very nice; it was my birthday gift.)
9. 你個銀包邊度買㗎？我想買一個同佢一樣。 (Where did you buy your wallet? I want to buy one just like it.)
10. 我個銀包入面有好多張信用卡，好麻煩。 (There are many credit cards in my wallet; it's quite troublesome.) [end of text]


